Package team1351.purepursuit

Class Path

  • java.lang.Object
    • Path
  • public class Path
extends java.lang.Object
    Master Path Object.

    Contains functions for generating the distance, curvature, and velocity for each point. Holds the master array of TrajectoryPoint for the path with calculated x, y, distance, curvature, and velocity values.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Owen Leather

      • maxAcceleration

        private double maxAcceleration

      • maxVelocity

        private double maxVelocity
        Maximum robot velocity value. This is used to make sure the velocity of each point does not go over the maximum velocity of the robot.

      • kCurvature

        private double kCurvature
        Value that determines how much the velocity slows down around turns. Decreasing this value makes the velocity slow down more around turns. This value is usually best around 0.8-2, 0.8 tends to slow down around almost any curvature in the path, and 2 tends to slow down around only very sharp curvature.

      • calculateCurvature

        public void calculateCurvature()
        Calculates the curvature for each point along the path.

        The curvature is used to slow down the robot's velocity around corners. The curvature calculation is done by taking the previous, current, and next point of the Path and fitting a circle through those points. The curvature is then 1/radius of the fit circle.

      • calculateVelocities

        public void calculateVelocities()
        Calculates the velocity for each point along the path.

        This makes sure the robot never accelerates faster than the maxAcceleration and never goes faster than maxVelocity. It also takes the curvature of each point into account to slow down the velocity around turning.

        The function starts by looping through the points backwards and calculating the velocity based on acceleration and curvature. Then it loops through the points forwards doing the same thing. The reason it loops through the points twice is because the algorithm for calculating the velocity based on acceleration only works on acceleration periods.

        public void setKCurvature​(double kCurvature)
        Sets the kCurvature value. kCurvature is how much the velocity slows down around turns. Decreasing this value makes the velocity slow down more around turns. This value is usually best around 0.8-2, 0.8 tends to slow down around almost any curvature in the path, and 2 tends to slow down around only very sharp curvature.
